Edna Marion https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edna_Marion 0 Edna Marion, also known as Edna Marian (born Edna Marion Hannam; December 12, 1906 – December 2, 1957) was a silent motion picture actress who appeared in a number of Hal Roach short comedies. Her death certificate states she was a housewife when she died in Los Angeles from pneumonia, and her death widowed her husband Harold Naisbitt. She is buried at Holy-Cross Cemetery, in Los Angeles CA.
